# Mobile-First Tarmac Application

This is a **mobile-first webapp** built with Symfony and Tabler.io. Always prioritize mobile experience first, then enhance for larger screens.

## Core Principles

### Mobile-First Design
- **Start with mobile**: Design and code for mobile screens (320px-768px) first
- **Progressive enhancement**: Add features for tablet (768px+) and desktop (1024px+) 
- **Touch-optimized**: All interactions must work perfectly on touch devices
- **Performance-first**: Optimize for mobile networks and slower devices

### Tabler.io Integration
- **Use Tabler components**: Leverage Tabler's mobile-optimized components
- **Follow Tabler patterns**: Use Tabler's responsive utilities and classes
- **Maintain consistency**: Stick to Tabler's design system and spacing
- **Customize when needed**: Extend Tabler styles for mobile-specific needs

## Development Guidelines

### Layout & Components
- **Single column** layouts on mobile by default
- **Card-based** designs for better mobile readability
- **Touch targets**: Minimum 44px × 44px for all interactive elements
- **Navigation**: Collapsible hamburger menu on mobile
- **Tables**: Card layout or horizontal scroll on mobile

### Typography & Spacing
- **Base font**: 16px minimum for mobile readability
- **Line height**: 1.5 for mobile, 1.4 for desktop
- **Spacing**: Use Tabler's spacing scale (4px, 8px, 16px, 24px, 32px)
- **Text scaling**: Support up to 200% zoom without horizontal scroll

### Performance Requirements
- **First Contentful Paint**: < 1.5s on 3G
- **Largest Contentful Paint**: < 2.5s on 3G
- **Cumulative Layout Shift**: < 0.1
- **Images**: WebP format with proper sizing
- **JavaScript**: Lazy load non-critical scripts

### Forms & Interactions
- **Full-width inputs** on mobile
- **Always visible labels** (not placeholder-only)
- **Touch-friendly controls** with proper spacing
- **Inline validation** that doesn't block interaction
- **Progressive enhancement**: Core functionality works without JS

### Testing & Quality
- **Real device testing**: iPhone SE, iPhone 12, Samsung Galaxy
- **Network testing**: 3G, 4G, WiFi conditions
- **Accessibility**: WCAG AA compliance, screen reader support
- **Cross-browser**: Chrome Mobile, Safari Mobile, Firefox Mobile

## Code Standards

### Twig Templates
- Use Tabler's responsive classes: `d-block d-md-none`, `d-none d-md-block`
- Implement mobile-first media queries: `@media (min-width: 768px)`
- Use semantic HTML5 elements with proper ARIA labels
- Keep templates DRY with includes and blocks

### CSS/Styling
- Extend Tabler styles in `/assets/styles/app.css`
- Use Tabler utility classes for rapid development
- Implement mobile-first media queries
- Critical CSS inlined for above-the-fold content

### JavaScript
- Use Stimulus controllers for interactive components
- Implement touch-friendly event handlers
- Debounce scroll and resize events
- Progressive enhancement approach

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid
- ❌ Desktop-first responsive design
- ❌ Fixed widths that don't scale
- ❌ Horizontal scrolling on mobile
- ❌ Tiny touch targets (< 44px)
- ❌ Hover states as primary interaction
- ❌ Complex multi-step forms
- ❌ Blocking JavaScript in head
- ❌ Large images without optimization

## Success Metrics
- **Mobile PageSpeed Score**: > 90
- **Mobile Lighthouse Score**: > 90
- **Time to Interactive**: < 3s on 3G
- **Bounce Rate**: < 40% on mobile
- **Task Completion**: > 85% on mobile

Remember: Every feature, component, and page must work perfectly on mobile first. Desktop and tablet experiences are enhancements, not the starting point.